        <h3 class="hed">Pluto Like You've Never Seen it Before</h3>
    </a>
    <ul class="metadata">
        <li class="byline"><a href="/author/alan-taylor/" title="Alan Taylor">Alan Taylor</a></li>
    </ul>

    <div class="article-content without-excerpt">
        <p class="dek"><span>Images from NASA&rsquo;s New Horizons spacecraft just </span>released today<span> show a backlit mountainous panorama of Pluto, displaying an amazing icy landscape never before seen by humans. </span><span>Just 15 minutes after its closest approach to Pluto on July 14, 2015, the spacecraft looked back toward the sun and captured this near-sunset view of icy mountains reaching heights of 11,000 feet above flat ice plains extending to Pluto&rsquo;s horizon.</span></p>
        
